## Early game

**Zeugma** on Phobos (Dark Sector Survival) is among the best Rubedo spots at
any gear level — the wiki cites roughly 250 Rubedo per 5 minutes there, and
Phobos is one of Rubedo's two signature planets. Rubedo drops from the enemies
you kill, so a Nekros loot squad and a Resource Drop Booster raise the yield on
top of the Dark Sector's resource-chance bonus.

## Mid & late game

The wiki's general endgame advice is simply "run Void Survival or Defense" —
it cites over 1,000 Rubedo per 20 minutes from Orokin Void endless missions.
**Ani** (Survival, Steel Path) is a standard Void node for putting that into
practice with a squad. Since Rubedo is a common enemy drop, the Steel Path
passive, a Resource Drop Booster and a loot frame (Nekros/Khora) all stack —
and the longer the run, the more enemies you clear.

